    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>To multiply a vector by a scalar \( k \), you multiply <b>each component</b> of the vector by \( k \).</p>

\[ k \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} k \times x \\ k \times y \end{pmatrix} \]

<p><b>Part (a):</b> Multiply by {@k1@}:</p>
\[ {@k1@} \begin{pmatrix} {@ax@} \\ {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@k1@} \times {@ax@} \\ {@k1@} \times {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@ta1[1][1]@} \\ {@ta1[2][1]@} \end{pmatrix} \]

<p><b>Part (b):</b> Multiply by {@k2@} (Negative reverses the direction):</p>
\[ {@k2@} \begin{pmatrix} {@ax@} \\ {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@k2@} \times {@ax@} \\ {@k2@} \times {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@ta2[1][1]@} \\ {@ta2[2][1]@} \end{pmatrix} \]

<p><b>Part (c):</b> Multiply by \(\frac{1}{2}\) (Halves the length):</p>
\[ \frac{1}{2} \begin{pmatrix} {@ax@} \\ {@ay@} \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@ax@} / 2 \\ {@ay@} / 2 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} {@ta3[1][1]@} \\ {@ta3[2][1]@} \end{pmatrix} \]]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
